#Text=What do you think Anonymous should do if Scientologists plant fake anons in a protest and act like idiots to show anons up ?
#Text=Scientologists pretending to be Anonymous at your pickets , that 's bound to happen .
#Text=That 's what Hubbard ordered .
#Text=Adopt a " suitable guise " and infiltrate an organization to collect intelligence .

column1: #Text=They also are logging this channel and watching every word here and anywhere else we speak about them .
#Text=As for the dopey comments , I understand completely that that is the power of being Anonymous on the net .
#Text=It allows you to say outrageous things with no repercussions .
#Text=It happens everywhere on the net and I am not offended .
#Text=People say things they would never say to your face .
#Text=Are you going to upload the old XenuTV movies ( RealVideo ) to Google Video or something similar ?
#Text=Will my old RealVideos be uploaded to Google ?
#Text=Yes .
#Text=I have been working on it but I have a full time job and tons of things going one which has only gotten worse since this thing started .
#Text=I was talking to Tory yesterday and she is overwhelmed by the emails she 's getting .
#Text=I look at them and have panic attacks that I have n't even been able to read all of mine yet let alone respond .
#Text=Questions from IRC users
#Text=As you know now , the Anonymous Protests was extremely huge , but we are planning a second round the 15th of March .
#Text=And I — a 12-year-old WILL attend , is that a good sign that so young a person wants to be involved , or is it a bad sign ?
#Text=Well , it 's good if you understand what you 're getting yourself into and your parents or guardians are aware as well .
#Text=Scientology is serious .
#Text=They wo n't harm you but they do n't play games either .
#Text=12-year-old kids get swept into Scientology 's Cadet Org and moved into the Sea Org shortly after .
#Text=That is far more dangerous to a 12-year-old than picketing fraud and abuse .
#Text=Can you put any of this in a historical context ?
#Text=Have you studied the history of Scientology in relation to its " parent " organizations ( cults praying on the elite ) in the 18th - 20th centuries ?
#Text=( Many of L. Ron Hubbard 's ideas were taken directly from OTO which he was a member of in his early life for example ) .
#Text=Hubbard did call Crowley his good friend but I doubt that he was seriously deep into it .
#Text=I think he stumbled into a situation at Jack Parson mansion in which he could live high off the rich guys cash and steal his hot girlfriend .

#Text=I think he probably enjoyed a good laugh at the satanic rituals he engaged in but it certainly informed his understanding of how to run such a group and how people can buy into any wacky belief system .
